        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 5. Sudanonautes granulatus (Balss, 1929) s.s. paralectotype from Bismarckburg, Togo (MNB Crust.8977). A. right chela, external view; B. left chela, external view. Sudanonautes umaji n. sp. holotype from Umaji, Nigeria (NMU 9.IV.1983). C. right chela, external view; D. left chela, external view. Sudanonautes koudougou n. sp. holotype from Koudougou, Côte d’Ivoire (NBL CRUS.D.35256). E. right chela, external view; F. left chela, external view. Right cheliped carpus and merus superior view of G. S. granulatus (Balss, 1929) s.s. (MNB Crust.8977); H. S. umaji n. sp. (NMU 9.IV.1983); I. S. koudougou n. sp. (NBL CRUS.D.35256). Scale bars: A, B = 6.2 mm, C, D = 8 mm, E, F= 3 mm, G–I = 4.9 mm. Figures E, F, and I are based on those originally published in Cumberlidge (1993a) and are reproduced here with the permission of Oxford University Press, the copyright owner of the Journal of Crustacean Biology." ;
